                                                                                            <p class="word-copy-lh-mb" style="line-height:normal;margin-bottom:12.0pt;"><a href="https://www.irenemarques.net/"><strong>Irene Marques</strong></a> is a bilingual (English and Portuguese) writer and lecturer at Toronto Metropolitan University in the Department of English. She holds a PhD in comparative literature from the University of Toronto. She has published eight books in various genres (novel, poetry, short fiction) and as an academic. Her novel <em>Uma Casa no Mundo</em> (Imprensa Nacional, 2021) won the Imprensa Nacional / Ferreira de Castro Prize in Portugal.</p>
