              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/book-reviews/incoherence-love-arturo-fontaines-y-entonces-teresa-will-h-corral" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Fontaine-anchor.jpg?itok=8bv4E42Y" width="250" height="175" alt="Arturo Fontaine with the cover to his book Y entonces Teresa" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

</div></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-richtitle"><p class="field-content"><a href="https://worldliteraturetoday.org/blog/book-reviews/incoherence-love-arturo-fontaines-y-entonces-teresa-will-h-corral">The Incoherence of Love: Arturo Fontaine’s <em>Y entonces Teresa</em></a>
</p></div><div class="views-field views-field-field-author"><span class="views-label views-label-field-author field-name-field-blogauthor">By</span><span class="field-content field-name-field-blogauthor"><a href="/author/will-h-corral" hreflang="en">Will H. Corral</a>
</span></div>
        </li>
              <li>
          <div><div>  <a href="/blog/book-reviews/self-book-made-expanded-memories-jose-luis-peixotos-homecoming-irene-marques" hreflang="en"><img loading="lazy" src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/styles/medium_thumbnail/public/Peixoto-anchor.jpg?itok=6Ra2D-B7" width="250" height="175" alt="José Luís Peixoto with the cover to his book Homecoming" typeof="foaf:Image" class="img-fluid image-style-medium-thumbnail" />

</a>

